A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 1 of Title 6 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to general
2 provisions relative to aviation, so as to provide the Department of Transportation with
3 authority over vertiports; to provide for definitions; to provide for related matters; to repeal
4 conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Chapter 1 of Title 6 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to general provisions
8 relative to aviation, is amended by revising Code Section 6-1-1, relating to powers and duties
9 of Department of Transportation â€” Aviation and aviation facilities generally, as follows:
10 "6-1-1.
11 (a) As used in this title, the term:
12 (1) 'Landing field' shall include a vertiport.
13 (2) 'Vertiport' means an area specifically designated and primarily used for the landing,
14 takeoff, and servicing of aircraft with a maximum takeoff weight of greater than 1,320
15 pounds that is capable of vertical takeoff and landing.
16 (b) The Department of Transportation shall have the following powers and duties:
